    excerpt: "Phoenix, a city known for its arid beauty and scorching summers, relies heavily on water from the Salt and Verde Rivers, supplemented by the distant Colorado River. While essential for life in the desert, this water, combined with Phoenix's expansive distribution system and naturally mineral-rich...",
