    excerpt: "Denver's water supply, primarily fed by pristine mountain snowmelt, often boasts a natural softness that many cities envy. Yet, the journey from the Rocky Mountains to your faucet isn't always smooth. An aging distribution system and occasional seasonal runoff can introduce complexities, affectin...",
