    content: "San Diego, a city renowned for its stunning coastline and vibrant culture, faces a unique challenge when it comes to its water supply. Unlike many cities that rely heavily on local reservoirs, San Diego imports the majority of its water from distant sources \u2013 primarily Northern California and the Colorado River. While this ensures a consistent supply in an arid region, it comes with a consequence: higher mineral content and elevated Total Dissolved Solids (TDS) levels.\n\nFor residents, this often translates to hard water stains on fixtures, cloudy dishes, dry skin, and a noticeable taste or odor in their tap water. It's a common complaint, and it's why many San Diegans look to professional water treatment solutions to improve their home's water quality. Among the local specialists addressing these concerns is **Whole-House Water Filtration**, a company dedicated to providing comprehensive filtration systems for homes and businesses across the city.",
