    excerpt: "Chicago. A city defined by its magnificent lakefront, drawing its lifeblood from the vast, fresh expanse of Lake Michigan. On the surface, our water appears clean, refreshing, and abundant. Yet, beneath the bustling streets and historic architecture, a silent concern persists: aging lead service ...",
